ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It is a great class for those how already master well methods for research. A very good way for starting into quantitative or data-related research.
I would recommend it to a fellow student.
I would definitely recommend this course to other students as a vitally important step in learning what these methods can and cannot do for you and how.
One of the most important classes you will take. Pay attention.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I learned a lot from the part on Causal graphs, controlling for confounds and colliders. I do regret that we did not have access to the Imbens and Rubin at the tine, as I did not feel quite at ease and later in the semester no longer had the time to read the material.Even if I have not had the time to read all the suggested readings, I will continue doing so as time permits and as I advance in my research.
